main event: On September 26th, 1952 in Butler, Missouri, a civilian reported observing 20-30 objects resembling a small cluster of stars. The objects were seen flying in a South to North direction, making three complete circles before heading east and disappearing into the clouds. The duration of the sighting was approximately 3 minutes.
interesting points: The description of the objects resembled a small cluster of stars, lighter to white in color, and in a formation similar to an inverted 'V'.
The objects were observed flying from South to North, making three complete circles, and then heading east before disappearing into the clouds.
The sighting lasted approximately 3 minutes, with the first and second sightings each lasting 40 seconds and the third lasting 30 seconds.
The official conclusion was that the observed objects were identified as 'OTHER: BIRDS', suggesting a possible misinterpretation of the sighting as bird observations.
Despite the official conclusion, there were no definitive configurations or details seen, and the observer's sincerity was acknowledged.
